docs.lead_paragraph: The European Union on Friday nominated Kristalina Georgieva, a Bulgarian economist, to replace Christine Lagarde as managing director of the International Monetary Fund after a tense selection process.

headline.main: European Union Nominates Kristalina Georgieva to Lead I.M.F.

docs.abstract: President Trump’s trade adviser frequently cited Ron Vara, a fictional source who was a critic of China, in his writings.

docs.lead_paragraph: Peter Navarro, a top White House trade adviser, has developed a reputation in Washington as a Rasputin-like China hawk who whispers anti-China musings in President Trump’s ear.

headline.main: Peter Navarro Invented an Expert for His Books, Based on Himself
headline.print_headline: Who Is Ron Vara? Trade Adviser Invents an Expert

docs.abstract: Allies and adversaries are seeking ways to avoid President Trump’s sanctions, which critics say have become a substitute for foreign policy.
docs.snippet: Allies and adversaries are seeking ways to avoid President Trump’s sanctions, which critics say have become a substitute for foreign policy.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s increasing reliance on economic sanctions to solve foreign policy problems is fueling concern that the United States is abusing its financial power and prompting some governments to seek ways to evade American measures.

headline.main: Trump’s Embrace of Sanctions Irks Allies and Prompts Efforts to Evade Measures
headline.print_headline: Friend and Foe Alike Seeking Workarounds For Trump’s Sanctions

docs.abstract: Looking to punish Cuba over its support for President Nicolás Maduro of Venezuela, the United States will ban airlines from servicing all cities besides Havana.
docs.snippet: Looking to punish Cuba over its support for President Nicolás Maduro of Venezuela, the United States will ban airlines from servicing all cities besides Havana.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Transportation Department announced Friday that it would suspend flights from the United States to nine airports in Cuba beginning in December. The policy will sever air service to every international airport there except the one in Havana.

headline.main: Trump Administration Cuts Flights to Most Cuban Airports
headline.print_headline: U.S. Limits Flights to Cuba Over Its Support of Venezuela

docs.abstract: The acting director of Immigration and Customs Enforcement said the focus would be on 2,000 family members who already have deportation orders.
docs.snippet: The acting director of Immigration and Customs Enforcement said the focus would be on 2,000 family members who already have deportation orders.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The acting director of the Immigration and Customs Enforcement agency said on Wednesday that he would follow through with plans to send agents into communities to round up and deport undocumented families, in the Trump administration’s latest attempt to deter large-scale migration of Central Americans to the southwest border.

headline.main: Immigration Agency Says It Plans Deportation Operation Aimed at Undocumented Families
headline.print_headline: About 2,000 Family Members  Are Focus of Deportation Plan

byline.original: By Zolan Kanno-Youngs and Miriam Jordan

docs.lead_paragraph: Migrant children detained at the border continue to sleep in cold cells without proper clothing or adequate food, a top Democratic lawmaker said on Thursday, accusing the Department of Homeland Security of blocking members of Congress from visiting the facilities.

headline.print_headline: Poor Conditions Persist for Migrant Children at Border Centers, Democrats Say

docs.abstract: The National Park Service has warned that President Trump’s border wall will significantly damage or destroy more than 20 archaeological sites in the Arizona desert.
docs.snippet: The National Park Service has warned that President Trump’s border wall will significantly damage or destroy more than 20 archaeological sites in the Arizona desert.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The construction of President Trump’s wall along the southwestern border will significantly damage or completely destroy more than 20 archaeological sites in a natural park in the heart of Arizona’s Sonoran Desert, according to a study conducted by the National Park Service.

headline.main: Park Service Says Archaeological Sites Are Imperiled by Border Wall
headline.print_headline: Archaeological Sites in Arizona Face a Threat: Border Wall Construction

docs.abstract: Mr. Comey, who oversaw the inquiry into ties between President Trump’s associates and Russia, said he knew of no illegal surveillance directed at the campaign.
docs.snippet: Mr. Comey, who oversaw the inquiry into ties between President Trump’s associates and Russia, said he knew of no illegal surveillance directed at the campaign.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAUSALITO, Calif. — The former F.B.I. director James B. Comey said on Thursday that he knew of no electronic surveillance aimed at the Trump campaign during the 2016 presidential election, defending the bureau after Attorney General William P. Barr asserted a day earlier that the bureau spied on the campaign as part of the Russia investigation.

headline.main: Comey Defends Trump Campaign Surveillance: ‘I Have Never Thought of That as Spying’
headline.print_headline: Difference Of Opinion On ‘Spying’ By the F.B.I.

docs.lead_paragraph: Mick Mulvaney, the acting White House chief of staff, asked officials in the budget office after President Trump’s July 25 call with the Ukrainian president whether there was a legal justification for withholding hundreds of millions of dollars in military aid to Ukraine, according to two people briefed on an internal White House review.
